# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To be accountable to or [[subordinate]] to (someone) in a [[hierarchy]]; to [[receive]] [[order]]s from (someone); to give [[official]] [[update]]s to (someone who is above oneself in a hierarchy).
#: {{ux|en|The financial director '''reports''' to the CEO.}}
#: ''Now that I've been promoted, I '''report to''' Benjamin, whom I loathe.''
# {{lb|en|politics|dated}} To return or present as the result of an examination or consideration of any matter officially referred.
#: {{ux|en|The committee '''reported''' the bill with amendments, or '''reported''' a new bill, or '''reported''' the results of an inquiry.}}
